\par Fabricate
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Transmutation
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Sor/Wiz 5
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, M
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  See text
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  Up to 10 cu. ft./level; see text
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  Instantaneous
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  None
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  No
\par You convert material of one sort into a product that is of the same material. Creatures or magic items cannot be created or transmuted by the }{\i\fs20\cf0 fabricate }{\fs20\cf0 spell. The quality of items made by this spell is commensurate w
ith the quality of material used as the basis for the new fabrication. If you work with a mineral, the target is reduced to 1 cubic foot per level instead of 10 cubic feet.
\par You must make an appropriate Craft check to fabricate articles requiring a high degree of craftsmanship.
\par Casting requires 1 round per 10 cubic feet (or 1 cubic foot) of material to be affected by the spell.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Material Component: }{\fs20\cf0 The original material, which costs the same amount as the raw materials required to craft the item to be created.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Faerie Fire
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Evocation [Light]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Drd 1
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, DF
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Long (400 ft. + 40 ft./level)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Area:}{\fs20\cf0  Creatures and objects within a 5-ft.-radius burst
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1 min./level (D)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  None
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes
\par A pale glow surrounds and outlines the subjects. Outlined subjects shed light as candles. Outlined creatures do not benefit from the concealment normally provided by darkness (though a 2nd-level or higher magical }{\i\fs20\cf0 darkness }{\fs20\cf0 
effect functions normally), }{\i\fs20\cf0 blur}{\fs20\cf0 , displacement, invisibility, or similar effects. The light is too dim to have any special effect on undead or dark-dwelling creatures vulnerable to light. The }{\i\fs20\cf0 faerie fire }{
\fs20\cf0 can be blue, green, or violet, according to your choice at the time of casting. The }{\i\fs20\cf0 faerie fire }{\fs20\cf0 does not cause any harm to the objects or creatures thus outlined.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 False Life
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Necromancy
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Sor/Wiz 2
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, M
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Personal
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  You
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1 hour/level or until discharged; see text
\par You harness the power of unlife to grant yourself a limited ability to avoid death. While this spell is in effect, you gain temporary hit points equal to 1d10 +1 per caster level (maximum +10).
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Material Component: }{\fs20\cf0 A small amount of alcohol or distilled spirits, which you use to trace certain sigils on your body during casting. These sigils cannot be seen once the alcohol or spirits evaporate.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 False Vision
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Illusion (Glamer)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Brd 5, Sor/Wiz 5, Trickery 5
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, M
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Touch
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Area:}{\fs20\cf0  40-ft.-radius emanation
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1 hour/level (D)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  None
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  No
\par Any divination (scrying) spell used to view anything within the area of this spell instead receives a false image (as the }{\i\fs20\cf0 major image }{\fs20\cf0 
spell), as defined by you at the time of casting. As long as the duration lasts, you can concentrate to change the image as desired. While you aren\rquote t concentrating, the image remains static.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Arcane Material Component: }{\fs20\cf0 The ground dust of a piece of jade worth at least 250 gp, which is sprinkled into the air when the spell is cast.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Fear
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Necromancy [Fear, Mind-Affecting]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Brd 3, Sor/Wiz 4
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, M
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  30 ft.
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Area:}{\fs20\cf0  Cone-shaped burst
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1 round/level or 1 round; see text
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will partial
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes
\par An invisible cone of terror causes each living creature in the area to become panicked unless it succeeds on a Will save. If cornered, a panicked creature begins cowering. If the Will save succeeds, the creature is shaken for 1 round.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Material Component: }{\fs20\cf0 Either the heart of a hen or a white feather.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Feather Fall
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Transmutation
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Brd 1, Sor/Wiz 1
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 free action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Targets:}{\fs20\cf0  One Medium or smaller freefalling object or creature/level, no two of which may be more than 20 ft. apart
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  Until landing or 1 round/level
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will negates (harmless) or Will negates (object)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes (object)
\par The affected creatures or objects fall slowly. }{\i\fs20\cf0 Feather fall }{\fs20\cf0 
instantly changes the rate at which the targets fall to a mere 60 feet per round (equivalent to the end of a fall from a few feet), and the subjects take no damage upon landing while the spell is in effect. How
ever, when the spell duration expires, a normal rate of falling resumes.
\par The spell affects one or more Medium or smaller creatures (including gear and carried objects up to each creature\rquote s maximum load) or objects, or the equivalent in larger creatures: A 
Large creature or object counts as two Medium creatures or objects, a Huge creature or object counts as two Large creatures or objects, and so forth.
\par You can cast this spell with an instant utterance, quickly enough to save yourself if you unexpectedly fal
l. Casting the spell is a free action, like casting a quickened spell, and it counts toward the normal limit of one quickened spell per round. You may even cast this spell when it isn\rquote t your turn.
\par This spell has no special effect on ranged weapons unless they are falling quite a distance. If the spell is cast on a falling item the object does half normal damage based on its weight, with no bonus for the height of the drop.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Feather fall }{\fs20\cf0 works only upon free-falling objects. It does not affect a sword blow or a charging or flying creature.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Feeblemind
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Enchantment (Compulsion) [Mind-Affecting]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Sor/Wiz 5
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, M
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range: }{\fs20\cf0 Medium (100 ft. + 10 ft./level)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  One creature
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  Instantaneous
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: }{\fs20\cf0 Will negates; see text
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes
\par If the target creature fails a Will saving throw, its Intelligence and Charisma scores each drop to 1. The affected creature is unable to use Intelligence- or Charisma-based skills, cast spells, understand language
, or communicate coherently. Still, it knows who its friends are and can follow them and even protect them. The subject remains in this state until a }{\i\fs20\cf0 heal}{\fs20\cf0 , }{\i\fs20\cf0 limited wish}{\fs20\cf0 , }{\i\fs20\cf0 miracle}{\fs20\cf0 
, or }{\i\fs20\cf0 wish }{\fs20\cf0 spell is used to cancel the effect of the }{\i\fs20\cf0 feeblemind}{\fs20\cf0 . A creature that can cast arcane spells, such as a sorcerer or a wizard, takes a \endash 4 penalty on its saving throw.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Material Component: }{\fs20\cf0 A handful of clay, crystal, glass, or mineral spheres.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Find the Path
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Divination
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Brd 6, Clr 6, Drd 6, Knowledge 6, Travel 6
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, F
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  3 rounds
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Personal or touch
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  You or creature touched
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  10 min./level
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  None or Will negates (harmless)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  No or Yes (harmless)
\par The recipient of this spell can find the shortest, most direct physical route to a specified destination, be it the way into or out of a locale. The locale can be outdoors, underground, or even inside a }{\i\fs20\cf0 maze }{\fs20\cf0 spell. }{\i\fs20\cf0 
Find the path }{\fs20\cf0 works with respect to locations, not objects or creatures at a locale. The location must be on the same plane as you are at the time of casting.
\par The spell enables the subject to sense the correct direction that will eventually lead it to its destination, indicating at appropriate times 
the exact path to follow or physical actions to take. For example, the spell enables the subject to sense trip wires or the proper word to bypass a }{\i\fs20\cf0 glyph of warding. }{\fs20\cf0 
The spell ends when the destination is reached or the duration expires, whichever comes first. }{\i\fs20\cf0 Find the path }{\fs20\cf0 can be used to remove the subject and its companions from the effect of a }{\i\fs20\cf0 maze }{\fs20\cf0 
spell in a single round.
\par This divination is keyed to the recipient, not its companions, and its effect does not predict or allow for the actions of creatures (including guardians).
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Focus: }{\fs20\cf0 A set of divination counters of the sort you favor.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Find Traps
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Divination
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Clr 2
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Personal
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  You
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1 min./level
\par You gain intuitive insight into the wo
rkings of traps. You can use the Search skill to detect traps just as a rogue can. In addition, you gain an insight bonus equal to one-half your caster level (maximum +10) on Search checks made to find traps while the spell is in effect.
\par Note that }{\i\fs20\cf0 find traps }{\fs20\cf0 grants no ability to disable the traps that you may find.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Finger of Death
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Necromancy [Death]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Drd 8, Sor/Wiz 7
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  One living creature
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  Instantaneous
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  Fortitude partial
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes
\par You can slay any one living creature within range. The target is entitled to a Fortitude saving throw to survive the attack. If the save is successful, the creature instead takes 3d6 points of damage +1 point per caster level (maximum +25).
\par The subject might die from damage even if it succeeds on its saving throw.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Fire Seeds
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Conjuration (Creation) [Fire]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Drd 6, Fire 6, Sun 6
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, M
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Touch
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Targets:}{\fs20\cf0  Up to four touched acorns or up to eight touched holly berries
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  10 min./level or until used
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  None or Reflex half; see text
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  No
\par Depending on the version of }{\i\fs20\cf0 fire seeds }{\fs20\cf0 you choose, you turn acorns into splash weapons that you or another character can throw, or you turn holly berries into bombs that you can detonate on command.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Acorn Grenades: }{\fs20\cf0 As many as four acorns turn into special splash weapons that can be hurled as far as 100 feet. A ranged touch atta
ck roll is required to strike the intended target. Together, the acorns are capable of dealing 1d6 points of fire damage per caster level (maximum 20d6), divided up among the acorns as you wish.
\par Each acorn explodes upon striking any hard surface. In additi
on to its regular fire damage, it deals 1 point of splash damage per die, and it ignites any combustible materials within 10 feet. A creature within this area that makes a successful Reflex saving throw takes only half damage; a creature struck directly i
s not allowed a saving throw.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Holly Berry Bombs: }{\fs20\cf0 You turn as many as eight holly berries into special bombs. The holly berries are usually placed by hand, since they are too light to make effective thrown weapons (they can be tossed only 5 feet). If you are
 within 200 feet and speak a word of command, each berry instantly bursts into flame, causing 1d8 points of fire damage +1 point per caster level to every creature in a 5-foot radius burst and igniting any combustible materials within 5 feet. A creature i
n the area that makes a successful Reflex saving throw takes only half damage.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Material Component: }{\fs20\cf0 The acorns or holly berries.
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Fire Shield
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Evocation [Fire or Cold]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Fire 5, Sor/Wiz 4, Sun 4
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, M/DF
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 standard action
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range:}{\fs20\cf0  Personal
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Target:}{\fs20\cf0  You
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  1 round/level (D)
\par This spell wreathes you in flame and causes damage to each creature that attacks you in melee. The flames also protect you from either cold-based or fire-based attacks (your choice).
\par Any creature striking you with its body or a handheld weapon deals normal damage, but at the same time the attacker takes 1d6 points of damage +1 point per caster level (maximum +15). This damage is either cold damage (if the }{\i\fs20\cf0 shield }{
\fs20\cf0 protects against fire-based attacks) or fire damage (if the }{\i\fs20\cf0 shield }{\fs20\cf0 
protects against cold-based attacks). If the attacker has spell resistance, it applies to this effect. Creatures wielding weapons with exceptional reach are not subject to this damage if they attack you.
\par When casting this spell, you appear to immolate yourself, but the flames are thin and wispy, giving off light equal to only half the illumination of a normal torch (10 feet). The color of the flames is determined randomly (50% chance of either color)
\emdash blue or green if the }{\i\fs20\cf0 chill shield }{\fs20\cf0 is cast, violet or blue if the }{\i\fs20\cf0 warm shield }{\fs20\cf0 is employed. The special powers of each version are as follows.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Warm Shield: }{\fs20\cf0 The flames are warm to the touch. You take only half damage from cold-based attacks. If such an attack allows a Reflex save for half damage, you take no damage on a successful save.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Chill Shield: }{\fs20\cf0 The flames are cool to the touch. You take only half damage from fire-based attacks. If such an attack allows a Reflex save for half damage, you take no damage on a successful save.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Arcane Material Component: }{\fs20\cf0 A bit of phosphorus for the }{\i\fs20\cf0 warm shield; }{\fs20\cf0 a live firefly or glowworm or the tail portions of four dead ones for the }{\i\fs20\cf0 chill shield}{\fs20\cf0 .
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Fire Storm
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Evocation [Fire]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Clr 8, Drd 7, Fire 7
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Casting Time:}{\fs20\cf0  1 round
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Range: }{\fs20\cf0 Medium (100 ft. + 10 ft./level)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Area:}{\fs20\cf0  Two 10-ft. cubes per level (S)
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Duration:}{\fs20\cf0  Instantaneous
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw:}{\fs20\cf0  Reflex half
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance:}{\fs20\cf0  Yes
\par When a }{\i\fs20\cf0 fire storm }{\fs20\cf0 spell is cast, the whole area is shot through with sheets of roaring flame. The raging flames do not har
m natural vegetation, ground cover, and any plant creatures in the area that you wish to exclude from damage. Any other creature within the area takes 1d6 points of fire damage per caster level (maximum 20d6).
\par 
\par }{\cf0 Fire Trap
\par }{\fs20\cf0 Abjuration [Fire]
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Level:}{\fs20\cf0  Drd 2, Sor/Wiz 4
\par }{\b\fs20\cf0 Components:}{\fs20\cf0  V, S, M
