on an item. Material objects not in use are always affected by this spell, while an object wielded or employed by a creature receives a Reflex saving throw to avoid the effect. If the initial saving throw fails, the creature immediately drops the item. A 
saving throw must be made in each round that the creature attempts to pick up or use the }{\i\fs20\cf0 greased }{\fs20\cf0 item. A creature wearing }{\i\fs20\cf0 greased }{\fs20\cf0 
