\par This powerful spell is primarily used to defend your stronghold. The ward protects 200 square feet per caster level. The warded area can be as much as 20 feet high, and shaped as you desire. You can ward several stories of a stronghold by dividing the are
a among them; you must be somewhere within the area to be warded to cast the spell. The spell creates the following magical effects within the warded area.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Fog: }{\fs20\cf0 Fog fills all corridors, obscuring all sight, including darkvision, beyond 5 feet. A creature wi
thin 5 feet has concealment (attacks have a 20% miss chance). Creatures farther away have total concealment (50% miss chance, and the attacker cannot use sight to locate the target). Saving Throw: None. Spell Resistance: No.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Arcane Locks: }{\fs20\cf0 All doors in the warded area are }{\i\fs20\cf0 arcane locked. }{\fs20\cf0 Saving Throw: None. Spell Resistance: No.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Webs: }{\fs20\cf0 Webs fill all stairs from top to bottom. These strands are identical with those created by the }{\i\fs20\cf0 web }{\fs20\cf0 spell, except that they regrow in 10 minutes if they are burned or torn away while the }{
\i\fs20\cf0 guards and wards }{\fs20\cf0 spell lasts. Saving Throw: Reflex negates; see text for }{\i\fs20\cf0 web}{\fs20\cf0 . Spell Resistance: No.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Confusion: }{\fs20\cf0 Where there are choices in direction\emdash such as a corridor intersection or side passage\emdash a minor }{\i\fs20\cf0 confusion-}{\fs20\cf0 type effect functions so as to ma
ke it 50% probable that intruders believe they are going in the opposite direction from the one they actually chose. This is an enchantment, mind-affecting effect. Saving Throw: None. Spell Resistance: Yes.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 Lost Doors: }{\fs20\cf0 One door per caster level is covered by a }{\i\fs20\cf0 silent image }{\fs20\cf0 to appear as if it were a plain wall. Saving Throw: Will disbelief (if interacted with). Spell Resistance: No.
\par In addition, you can place your choice of one of the following five magical effects.
\par 1. }{\i\fs20\cf0 Dancing lights }{\fs20\cf0 in four corridors. You can designate a simple program that causes the lights to repeat as long as the }{\i\fs20\cf0 guards and wards }{\fs20\cf0 spell lasts. Saving Throw: None. Spell Resistance: No.
\par 2. A }{\i\fs20\cf0 magic mouth }{\fs20\cf0 in two places. Saving Throw: None. Spell Resistance: No.
\par 3. A }{\i\fs20\cf0 stinking cloud }{\fs20\cf0 in two places. The vapors appear in the places you designate; they return within 10 minutes if dispersed by wind while the }{\i\fs20\cf0 guards and wards }{\fs20\cf0 
spell lasts. Saving Throw: Fortitude negates; see text for }{\i\fs20\cf0 stinking cloud. }{\fs20\cf0 Spell Resistance: No.
\par 4. A }{\i\fs20\cf0 gust of wind }{\fs20\cf0 in one corridor or room. Saving Throw: Fortitude negates. Spell Resistance: Yes.
\par 5. A }{\i\fs20\cf0 suggestion }{\fs20\cf0 in one place. You select an area of up to 5 feet square, and any creature who enters or passes through the area receives the }{\i\fs20\cf0 suggestion }{\fs20\cf0 mentally. Saving Throw: Will negates
. Spell Resistance: Yes.
